      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material and geometric inputs traceable to measured values with documented uncertainty; sensitivity analysis performed for key parameters.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate strength sourced from lot-specific tensile testing (N=5 coupons). Geometric dimensions measured by CMM on production screws. Sensitivity analysis identified yield strength and rod diameter as the two most influential parameters; their uncertainties are propagated through the model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test constructs from production-representative hardware; N≥10 specimens across at least two independent test sites.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production hardware were tested: six at Laboratory 1 (FDA) and five at Laboratory 2 (DePuy Synthes). Constructs are representative of the intended commercial configuration. Inter-laboratory variability was within 4% for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two independent loading conditions or environments representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single loading configuration (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending at 5 mm/min). Only one test condition was evaluated, which falls short of the required level. This is a known limitation acknowledged in the credibility assessment; the shortfall is offset by the multi-laboratory sample strategy and the direct correspondence of the test condition to the regulatory submission loading scenario."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA input parameters matched to experimentally measured values within stated tolerances; documented parameter mapping table provided.",
      "rationale": "A parameter mapping table was prepared cross-referencing each FEA input to its experimental measurement source. Geometric dimensions input to the FEA were taken from CMM measurements of the actual test articles. Material parameters were matched to lot-specific coupon data. All mapped values fell within ±2% of nominal."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs across all three modeling teams.",
      "rationale": "All three modeling teams achieved E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. The highest E/uval observed was 1.41 (yield force, Team 2). Percent differences ranged from 1.2% to 8.7%. Pre-established acceptance bounds are met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to regulatory submission acceptance criteria and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in FDA guidance for pedicle screw construct evaluation. Each QoI is directly linked to a clinical failure mode: stiffness to load-sharing behavior, yield force to permanent deformation risk, and force at 40 mm to catastrophic fracture risk."
